The article discusses the importance of civic engagement and volunteer service in strengthening the United States. It highlights National Volunteer Week as an opportunity to recognize and honor individuals who selflessly invest in the lives of others. The article acknowledges the contributions of volunteers in various organizations and their ability to foster kindness and goodwill in communities. It also emphasizes the significance of volunteerism during the COVID-19 pandemic, as Americans are coming together to help those in need. The article urges people to join in volunteering efforts, including donating blood, to address critical needs. President Donald J. Trump proclaims April 19-25, 2020, as National Volunteer Week and encourages Americans to make service a part of their daily lives.